</ClauseTitle><ClauseText id="1126272"><SubSection id="1166182">
<SubSection_PgfTag id="1202396"><PgfNumString><PgfNumString_1>(1)</PgfNumString_1> </PgfNumString><SubSection_text><ParaLineStart LineNum="16"></ParaLineStart>A classification certificate issued in respect of a video work may be <ParaLineStart LineNum="17"></ParaLineStart>issued so as to have effect only for the purposes of a video recording <ParaLineStart LineNum="18"></ParaLineStart>that is described in the certificate (whether by reference to its <ParaLineStart LineNum="19"></ParaLineStart>contents, to the manner in which it is, or is to be, supplied or <ParaLineStart LineNum="20"></ParaLineStart>otherwise).</SubSection_text></SubSection_PgfTag>
</SubSection>
<SubSection id="1172977">
<SubSection_PgfTag id="1202400"><PgfNumString><PgfNumString_1>(2)</PgfNumString_1> </PgfNumString><SubSection_text><ParaLineStart LineNum="21"></ParaLineStart>For the purposes of this Act, a video recording contains a video work <ParaLineStart LineNum="22"></ParaLineStart>in respect of which a classification certificate has been issued if (and <ParaLineStart LineNum="23"></ParaLineStart>only if) a classification certificate that has been issued in respect of <ParaLineStart LineNum="24"></ParaLineStart>the video work has effect for the purposes of the video recording.”</SubSection_text></SubSection_PgfTag>
</SubSection>
</ClauseText>
